# Linear Task Tracking

- Canonical note: `docs/30-Implementation/linear-task-tracking.md`. This rule is an
  orchestrator; if it disagrees with that note, the vault wins.
- Tracker: **Linear, team FMX** (<https://linear.app/coding-x/team/FMX/active>),
  project *Phase 1 — Research & Architecture*. Linear = operational status, vault =
  durable knowledge — never duplicate.
- Issues: title `Verb + area + object`; body Summary / Context (+vault links) /
  Requirements / Acceptance; mandatory one `type:` + one `area:` label; link the
  canonical vault note. Agents create only in `Backlog`, search for duplicates
  first, max 3 new issues/session, and never change labels/states.
- Status moves by agents: claim `Backlog` or `Todo` by immediately moving the
  issue to `In Progress` after verifying no active branch/PR/worktree already owns
  it; then `In Progress → In Review`, or `→ Blocked` (with a comment). **Never**
  move to `Done`/`Canceled` — Nico only.
- Branch carries the Linear ID: `feat/fmx-<n>-<slug>` (human),
  `claude|codex|cursor/fmx-<n>-<slug>` (agent). PR title `[FMX-<n>] …`; PR body
  first line `Closes FMX-<n>` (docs/non-closing: `Part of FMX-<n>`).
- Priority = Linear's native field, not a label.
